channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Andrew Yang Is Either Smoking Something or Working to Get Back Into the Dem Party's Good Graces
Supreme Court to release crucial Trump immunity decision, 'a rule for the ages'
item.description: The Supreme Court will hand down a ruling Monday regarding whether former President Trump enjoys immunity in his election interference case.

item.title: US Supreme Court to Rule on Debit Card 'Swipe Fees'
item.description: The U.S. Supreme Court is expected Monday to decide a case involving a legal challenge to a Federal Reserve regulation on debit card "swipe fees" in a ruling that could make it easier for businesses to try to overturn longstanding federal rules.

item.title: Biden Team Sends Out Desperate Email Describing How to Defend Him, Attack 'Bedwetting Brigade'
New Florida law establishes safe space in sheriff's office parking lots for child custody exchanges
item.description: A new law in Florida taking effect on Monday creates designated safe areas at sheriff's offices for separated parents to exchange their children in accordance with their custody plans.

item.title: Graham: Retribution Against Dems if Trump Wins
item.description: Sen. Lindsey Graham, R-S.C., warned that retribution against Democrats would come if former President Donald Trump wins in November.

item.title: Mom of War Hero Pat Tillman Furious ESPN Anointed Prince Harry Winner of Award Named After Her Son
Chinese military AI in focus as lawmaker sounds alarm on threat from rifle-wielding 'robot-dogs'
item.description: An amendment to the 2025 NDAA from Florida Congressman Vern Buchanan focuses on the threat from Chinese military AI robot-dogs that can wield rifles.

item.title: Van Jones: Harris Likely President if Biden Wins
item.description: On Friday, CNN's Van Jones, during a broadcast of "CNN NewsNight," suggested that President Joe Biden would not be able to endure another four years as president and, if he's reelected, Vice President Kamala Harris would take his place.

item.title: Former WH Photographer Spills the Beans, Details How Biden Aides Hide His Decline From the Public
'AI for Mayor': Wyoming man speaks out after intel firm throws roadblock in bot's landmark campaign
item.description: Victor Miller, the man behind Cheyenne mayoral candidate 'VIC', saw his AI bot somewhat blocked by technology firm OpenAI on Thursday, leading him to reassess.

item.title: Biden's Family Urges Him To Stay, Says He Should Axe Advisers
item.description: President Joe Biden's family members privately trashed his campaign advisers this weekend at Camp David, blamed them for his failure in Thursday's debate, and urged Biden to either fire or demote people.

item.title: US Bases in Europe Put on High Readiness to Deal With Intelligence Warning of Terror Attack
‘Woke’ universities put on notice for allowing ‘disgraceful mob riots’ in new GOP bill
item.description: A new House GOP bill would force colleges and universities to come up with and comply with regulations to deal with civil disobedience.

item.title: Biden's Debate Performance 'Shocked' WH Staff
item.description: After the fallout of Thursday night's debate hosted by CNN, there are multiple media reports that White House staff were shocked at President Joe Biden's performance against former President Donald Trump.
